      <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
         
        <tr>
          <td width="3%" valign="top">(ii)</td>
          <td width="97%">
<p align="justify"> An individual includes his or her heirs, executors, 
            administrators and assigns;</p><br></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td width="3%" valign="top">(iii)</td>
          <td width="97%">
<p align="justify"> A firm includes its partners for the time being 
            of the firm their respective heirs, executors, administrators and 
            assigns and/or the surviving partners;</p><br></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td width="3%" valign="top">(iv)</td>
          <td width="97%"> 
            <p align="justify"> A company include its successors and assigns;<br>
            </p>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td width="3%" valign="top">(v) </td>
          <td width="97%"> 
            <p align="justify">A joint and undivided Hindu family or a joint family firm include 
            its co-parceners;</p></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td width="3%">&nbsp;</td>
          <td width="97%">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
		 <tr>
          <td width="3%">&nbsp;</td>
          <td width="97%">IT IS HEREBY AGREED between the borrower and bank as 
            follows :</td>
        </tr> <tr>
          <td width="3%">&nbsp;</td>
          <td width="97%">&nbsp;</td>
        </tr>
		 <tr>
          <td width="3%" valign="top">(ii) </td>
          <td width="97%"><p align="justify">This modification agreement shall be supplemental to 
            the hypothecation agreement dtd. __________ executed by the borrower 
            along with other security documents to secure credit facilities mentioned 
            in Schedule &#145;A&#146; hereunder written.</p><br></td>
        </tr>
		 <tr>
          <td width="3%" valign="top">(iii)</td>
          <td width="97%"> <p align="justify">The Borrower will be entitled to convert the entire 
            WCDL credit facility into FCL credit facility and avail the same at 
            any one time. However, if borrower opts for conversion of the WCDL 
            facility in part or to the extent of the unavailed portion of WCDL 
            credit facility, he will be entitled to convert the balance of WCDL 
            credit facility in FCL credit facility, after adjusting the dues in 
            respect of WCDL credit facility, if any, at any time after the execution 
            of this Agreement, to the extent of the limit of FCL credit facility 
            mentioned in Schedule &#145;A&#146; hereunder written. If the Borrower 
            desires to avail the balance FCL credit facility, then the Borrower 
            shall make a fresh application and the Bank shall be at liberty to 
            consider the same in terms of the then prevailing RBI or Government 
            directions and subject to the foreign exchange availability at that 
            time. It is specifically agreed by the Borrower that the Bank will 
            be entitled to grant/ refuse the same in its sole direction and if 
            granted shall be on such conditions as the bank may deem fit including 
            charging the interest at such rate as the Bank may decide and/or on 
            execution of such documents including this Agreement, as may be necessary 
            in the opinion of the Bank.</p><br></td>
        </tr>
		 <tr>
          <td width="3%" valign="top">(iv)</td>
          <td width="97%"><p align="justify"> The borrower agrees/confirms that on the borrower&#146;s 
            request the Bank has converted in part/full the rupee component of 
            Rs. _________ into US $ __________, out of WCDL credit facility more 
            particularly described in column III of Schedule &#145;A&#146; hereunder 
            written.</p><br></td>
        </tr> <tr>
          <td width="3%" valign="top">(v)</td>
          <td width="97%"> <p align="justify">The Borrower confirms that the said FCL facility is 
            secured by Agreement of Hypothecation/pledge/mortgage and accept the 
            aforesaid conversion into US $. The other terms and conditions governing 
            the said C.C. (H) credit facility/limits mentioned in Schedule &#145;A&#146; 
            shall continue to be operative and binding on the borrower.</p><br></td>
        </tr>
		<tr>
          <td width="3%" valign="top">(vi)</td>
          <td width="97%"><p align="justify"> The Borrower agrees to repay the converted loan of 
            US Dollars ___________ together with interest in US Dollars as per 
            the scheme approved by RBI in this behalf.</p><br></td>
        </tr><tr>
          <td width="3%" valign="top">(vii) </td>
          <td width="97%"> 
           <p align="justify"> The borrower agrees to repay the aforesaid loan of US Dollars ____________ 
            within _________ days and further agrees to pay the interest at ____% 
            over LIBOR rate fixed at six monthly intervals viz. _____________ 
            and _____________ with quarterly rests in US Dollars.</p><br></td>
        </tr><tr>
          <td width="3%" valign="top">(viii)</td>
          <td width="97%"> 
            <p align="justify">The Borrower hereby agrees to execute fresh Demand Promissory Note/(s) 
            undertaking/(s) to pay _________ US Dollars in addition/substitution/ 
            modification of the Demand Promissory Note dated <b> <%=Helper.correctNull((String) hshValues.get("Curdate"))%></b>  executed 
            by him securing repayment of the advance permitted under FCL credit 
            facility mentioned in Schedule A, or part thereof together with interest</p><br>
          </td>
        </tr><tr>
          <td width="3%" valign="top">(ii) </td>
          <td width="97%"><p align="justify">The Borrower shall repay the outstandings under FCL 
            credit facility including principal and interest within 180 days from 
            the date of disbursal of the loan under FCL credit facility.</p><br></td>
        </tr><tr>
          <td width="3%" valign="top">(ii)</td>
          <td width="97%"><p align="justify"> In the event of the Borrower unable to repay the said 
            outstandings under FCL credit facility within 180 days as aforesaid, 
            he shall make an application to the Bank atleast 15 days in advance 
            to roll over the outstandings under the said loan granted under FCL 
            credit facility for further period of 180 days or for such other period 
            as the Bank may decide but subject to the terms and conditions as 
            the Bank may deem fit and subject to the availability of foreign exchange 
            and the rate of interest as may be prevailing then.</p><br></td>
        </tr><tr>
          <td width="3%" valign="top">(iii) </td>
          <td width="97%"> 
            <p align="justify">The Borrower hereby agrees/undertakes to comply with the necessary 
            statutory formalities and the RBI guidelines/directives from time 
            to time.</p><br></td>
        </tr><tr>
          <td width="3%" valign="top">(iv) </td>
          <td width="97%"> 
           <p align="justify"> The Borrower agrees to abide by the terms of FCL credit facility in 
            the manner mentioned in the letter of undertaking given by the borrower 
            and/or sanction letter of the Bank, sanctioning the said FCL credit 
            facility and agrees that the same shall form part of this agreement.</p><br> 
          </td>
        </tr><tr>
          <td width="3%" valign="top">(v) </td>
          <td width="97%" > 
           <p align="justify">On adjustment of the Foreign Currency Loan availed by the borrower 
            with interest under FCL credit facility, the borrower shall be eligible 
            to apply for a fresh loan under FCL credit facility and the Bank will 
            consider the same depending on the circumstances then prevailing and 
            on such terms and conditions as the Bank may deem fit. The Bank may 
            however grant or refuse the same in its sole discretion.</p><br>
          </td>
        </tr><tr>
          <td width="3%" valign="top">(vi)</td>
          <td width="97%"> 
           <p align="justify"> The Bank will be entitled to withdraw the FCL credit facility at any 
            time, and on such withdrawal, the borrower shall be liable to adjust 
            the outstandings under the said facility in US Dollars on the demand 
            being made by the Bank, forthwith.</p> <br>
          </td>
        </tr><tr>
          <td width="3%" valign="top">(ii)</td>
          <td width="97%"><p align="justify">The Borrower agrees that the terms as contained in this 
            Agreement shall be in addition to the terms and conditions contained 
            in Hypothecation Agreement dated <b> <%=Helper.correctNull((String) hshValues.get("Curdate"))%></b> executed by the borrower. 
            However, in case of FCL credit facility, the rate of interest shall 
            be related to LIBOR rate of interest and repayment of the principal 
            and interest shall be in US Dollars only.</p><br></td>
        </tr><tr>
          <td width="3%" valign="top">(iii)</td>
          <td width="97%"><p align="justify"> The Borrower agrees that the Bank will be at liberty 
            to take such steps as may be necessary for covering exchange risk 
            including upon the Borrower to adjust a part of FCL credit facility, 
            and/or increasing the margin provided by the Borrower and/or providing 
            additional securities.</p><br>
          </td>
        </tr><tr>
          <td width="3%" valign="top"> (iv) </td>
          <td width="97%"><p align="justify">In case of borrower&#146;s default to repay the foreign 
            currency loan together with interest within 180 days or as per the 
            terms of this Agreement, the Bank shall at its option may convert 
            the foreign currency loan into Indian rupees at the rate of exchange 
            prevailing on the 180th day and the borrower shall accept his liability 
            to repay the said loan in Indian Rupees for the said amount so informed 
            to him by the Bank and forthwith repay the same and till then the 
            outstanding under FCL Loan shall stand secured and charged by the 
            securities created under the agreement of hypothecation/pledge/mortgage 
            dated <b> <%=Helper.correctNull((String) hshValues.get("Curdate"))%></b>.</p><br></td>
        </tr><tr>
          <td width="3%" valign="top">(v)</td>
          <td width="97%"> 
            <p align="justify">In case of borrower&#146;s default in payment of foreign currency 
            loan in US Dollars and/or in Indian Rupees at the option of the Bank 
            as aforesaid, the Bank shall be at liberty to proceed against the 
            borrower for recovery of the dues outstanding as per the provisions 
            of Agreement of Hypothecation dated <b> <%=Helper.correctNull((String) hshValues.get("Curdate"))%></b>.</p><br> </td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      
    </td>
  </tr>
